Information:

Docker -> Postgre connection:
1. Install image of docker
2. docker run -d --name postgre -p 5432:5432 -v pg-data:/var/lib/postgresql/data postgres:latest
	-> -d (run as deamon)
	-> --name postgre (give name to container)
	-> -p 5432:5432 (from which port to which port)
	-> -v pg-data:/var/lib/postgresql/data (in which volume it will be used)
	-> postgres:latest (container Id)
3. docker exec -it <postgre container id> /bin/sh (get in the container inside)
4. psql -U postgres (inside the postgresql, now create table etc)
5. docker inspect <container_id>
6. Take IP and login via pgadmin

Role creation on docker:
1. docker exec -it <postgre container id> /bin/sh -> login to docker
2. psql -U postgres
3. \l -> see list of databases
4. CREATE ROLE burak superuser;
5. ALTER ROLE burak WITH LOGIN;
6. ALTER DATABASE cities OWNER TO burak;



Docker -> Tomcat installer
1. docker run -it -d -p 8888:8080 tomcat:latest
2. connect via localhost:8888
3. docker cp sample3.war <container id>:/usr/local/tomcat/webapps/

